[Name] ZeroMQ
[Summary] socket library that acts as a concurrency framework
[Description] ZeroMQ is a library that acts as a concurrency framework.
It carries messages across inproc, IPC, TCP, and multicast.
It is able to connect N-to-N via fanout, pubsub, pipeline, request-reply.
It's fast enough for clustered products and supercomputing
and provides asynch I/O for scalable multicore message-passing apps.
